verses.text_plain: Save me, O God; for the waters are come in unto my soul.
verses.verse_html: 1Save me, O God; for the waters are come in unto my soul.

verses.text_plain: I sink in deep mire, where there is no standing: I am come into deep waters, where the floods overflow me.
verses.verse_html:
2I sink in deep mire, where there is no standing: I am come into deep waters, where the floods overflow me. ▼
▼ deep mire: Heb. the mire of depth
 , ▼
▼ deep waters: Heb. depth of waters

footnotes.body_text: ▼ deep mire: Heb. the mire of depth
footnotes.body_html: ▼ deep mire: Heb. the mire of depth

footnotes.body_text: ▼ deep waters: Heb. depth of waters
footnotes.body_html: ▼ deep waters: Heb. depth of waters

verses.text_plain: I am weary of my crying: my throat is dried: mine eyes fail while I wait for my God.
verses.verse_html: 3I am weary of my crying: my throat is dried: mine eyes fail while I wait for my God.

verses.text_plain: They that hate me without a cause are more than the hairs of mine head: they that would destroy me, being mine enemies wrongfully, are mighty: then I restored that which I took not away.
verses.verse_html: 4They that hate me without a cause are more than the hairs of mine head: they that would destroy me, being mine enemies wrongfully, are mighty: then I restored that which I took not away.

verses.text_plain: O God, thou knowest my foolishness; and my sins are not hid from thee.
verses.verse_html:
5O God, thou knowest my foolishness; and my sins are not hid from thee. ▼
▼ sins: Heb. guiltiness

verses.text_plain: Let not them that wait on thee, O Lord God of hosts, be ashamed for my sake: let not those that seek thee be confounded for my sake, O God of Israel.
verses.verse_html: 6Let not them that wait on thee, O Lord God of hosts, be ashamed for my sake: let not those that seek thee be confounded for my sake, O God of Israel.

tokens.text: for my sake: let not those that seek

verses.text_plain: Because for thy sake I have borne reproach; shame hath covered my face.
verses.verse_html: 7Because for thy sake I have borne reproach; shame hath covered my face.

tokens.text: Because for thy sake I have borne

verses.text_plain: I am become a stranger unto my brethren, and an alien unto my mother’s children.
verses.verse_html: 8I am become a stranger unto my brethren, and an alien unto my mother’s children.

verses.text_plain: For the zeal of thine house hath eaten me up; and the reproaches of them that reproached thee are fallen upon me.
verses.verse_html: 9For the zeal of thine house hath eaten me up; and the reproaches of them that reproached thee are fallen upon me.

verses.text_plain: When I wept, and chastened my soul with fasting, that was to my reproach.
verses.verse_html: 10When I wept, and chastened my soul with fasting, that was to my reproach.

verses.text_plain: I made sackcloth also my garment; and I became a proverb to them.
verses.verse_html: 11I made sackcloth also my garment; and I became a proverb to them.

verses.text_plain: They that sit in the gate speak against me; and I was the song of the drunkards.
verses.verse_html:
12They that sit in the gate speak against me; and I was the song of the drunkards. ▼
▼ drunkards: Heb. drinkers of strong drink

footnotes.body_text: ▼ drunkards: Heb. drinkers of strong drink
footnotes.body_html: ▼ drunkards: Heb. drinkers of strong drink

verses.text_plain: But as for me, my prayer is unto thee, O Lord, in an acceptable time: O God, in the multitude of thy mercy hear me, in the truth of thy salvation.
verses.verse_html: 13But as for me, my prayer is unto thee, O Lord, in an acceptable time: O God, in the multitude of thy mercy hear me, in the truth of thy salvation.

tokens.text: But as for me, my prayer

verses.text_plain: Deliver me out of the mire, and let me not sink: let me be delivered from them that hate me, and out of the deep waters.
verses.verse_html: 14Deliver me out of the mire, and let me not sink: let me be delivered from them that hate me, and out of the deep waters.

tokens.text: me, and out of the deep

verses.text_plain: Let not the waterflood overflow me, neither let the deep swallow me up, and let not the pit shut her mouth upon me.
verses.verse_html: 15Let not the waterflood overflow me, neither let the deep swallow me up, and let not the pit shut her mouth upon me.

verses.text_plain: Hear me, O Lord; for thy lovingkindness is good: turn unto me according to the multitude of thy tender mercies.
verses.verse_html: 16Hear me, O Lord; for thy lovingkindness is good: turn unto me according to the multitude of thy tender mercies.

tokens.text: unto me according to the multitude

verses.text_plain: And hide not thy face from thy servant; for I am in trouble: hear me speedily.
verses.verse_html:
17And hide not thy face from thy servant; for I am in trouble: hear me speedily. ▼
▼ hear…: Heb. make haste to hear me

footnotes.body_text: ▼ hear…: Heb. make haste to hear me
footnotes.body_html: ▼ hear…: Heb. make haste to hear me

verses.text_plain: Draw nigh unto my soul, and redeem it: deliver me because of mine enemies.
verses.verse_html: 18Draw nigh unto my soul, and redeem it: deliver me because of mine enemies.

verses.text_plain: Thou hast known my reproach, and my shame, and my dishonour: mine adversaries are all before thee.
verses.verse_html: 19Thou hast known my reproach, and my shame, and my dishonour: mine adversaries are all before thee.

verses.text_plain: Reproach hath broken my heart; and I am full of heaviness: and I looked for some to take pity, but there was none; and for comforters, but I found none.
verses.verse_html:
20Reproach hath broken my heart; and I am full of heaviness: and I looked for some to take pity, but there was none; and for comforters, but I found none. ▼
▼ to take…: Heb. to lament with me

tokens.text: and I am full of heaviness

footnotes.body_text: ▼ to take…: Heb. to lament with me
footnotes.body_html: ▼ to take…: Heb. to lament with me

verses.text_plain: They gave me also gall for my meat; and in my thirst they gave me vinegar to drink.
verses.verse_html: 21They gave me also gall for my meat; and in my thirst they gave me vinegar to drink.

verses.text_plain: Let their table become a snare before them: and that which should have been for their welfare, let it become a trap.
verses.verse_html: 22Let their table become a snare before them: and that which should have been for their welfare, let it become a trap.

verses.text_plain: Let their eyes be darkened, that they see not; and make their loins continually to shake.
verses.verse_html: 23Let their eyes be darkened, that they see not; and make their loins continually to shake.

verses.text_plain: Pour out thine indignation upon them, and let thy wrathful anger take hold of them.
verses.verse_html: 24Pour out thine indignation upon them, and let thy wrathful anger take hold of them.

tokens.text: upon them, and let thy wrathful

verses.text_plain: Let their habitation be desolate; and let none dwell in their tents.
verses.verse_html:
25Let their habitation be desolate; and let none dwell in their tents. ▼
▼ their habitation: Heb. their palace
 , ▼
▼ let none…: Heb. let there not be a dweller

footnotes.body_html: ▼ their habitation: Heb. their palace

footnotes.body_text: ▼ let none…: Heb. let there not be a dweller
footnotes.body_html: ▼ let none…: Heb. let there not be a dweller

verses.text_plain: For they persecute him whom thou hast smitten; and they talk to the grief of those whom thou hast wounded.
verses.verse_html:
26For they persecute him whom thou hast smitten; and they talk to the grief of those whom thou hast wounded. ▼
▼ those…: Heb. thy wounded

tokens.text: of those whom thou hast wounded

footnotes.body_html: ▼ those…: Heb. thy wounded

verses.text_plain: Add iniquity unto their iniquity: and let them not come into thy righteousness.
verses.verse_html:
27Add iniquity unto their iniquity: and let them not come into thy righteousness. ▼
▼ iniquity unto…: or, punishment of iniquity, etc

footnotes.body_text: ▼ iniquity unto…: or, punishment of iniquity, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ iniquity unto…: or, punishment of iniquity, etc

verses.text_plain: Let them be blotted out of the book of the living, and not be written with the righteous.
verses.verse_html: 28Let them be blotted out of the book of the living, and not be written with the righteous.

verses.text_plain: But I am poor and sorrowful: let thy salvation, O God, set me up on high.
verses.verse_html: 29But I am poor and sorrowful: let thy salvation, O God, set me up on high.

verses.text_plain: I will praise the name of God with a song, and will magnify him with thanksgiving.
verses.verse_html: 30I will praise the name of God with a song, and will magnify him with thanksgiving.

verses.text_plain: This also shall please the Lord better than an ox or bullock that hath horns and hoofs.
verses.verse_html: 31This also shall please the Lord better than an ox or bullock that hath horns and hoofs.

verses.text_plain: The humble shall see this, and be glad: and your heart shall live that seek God.
verses.verse_html:
32The humble shall see this, and be glad: and your heart shall live that seek God. ▼
▼ humble: or, meek

verses.text_plain: For the Lord heareth the poor, and despiseth not his prisoners.
verses.verse_html: 33For the Lord heareth the poor, and despiseth not his prisoners.

verses.text_plain: Let the heaven and earth praise him, the seas, and every thing that moveth therein.
verses.verse_html:
34Let the heaven and earth praise him, the seas, and every thing that moveth therein. ▼
▼ moveth: Heb. creepeth

verses.text_plain: For God will save Zion, and will build the cities of Judah: that they may dwell there, and have it in possession.
verses.verse_html: 35For God will save Zion, and will build the cities of Judah: that they may dwell there, and have it in possession.

tokens.text: there, and have it in possession

verses.text_plain: The seed also of his servants shall inherit it: and they that love his name shall dwell therein.
verses.verse_html: 36The seed also of his servants shall inherit it: and they that love his name shall dwell therein.
